From 525e6770eb8cfe7ee5c6ca72c1c6ae2a4bf2f45c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: xylitol <xylitol@localhost>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 20:43:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] perry: re-inline pronto WLAN driver
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

perry_defconfig builds pronto as a module, but nothing in the 18.1
userspace loads /vendor/lib/modules/wlan.ko (official trees expect the
driver built in — see 612c0467 doing the same for cedric), so wlan0
never exists and the Wi-Fi HAL fails to create its STA iface.

Verified on device: manual insmod of the shipped wlan.ko brings up
firmware and wlan0 immediately. Match cedric/official with =y so the
driver is present before the HALs start.
---
 arch/arm64/configs/perry_defconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/configs/perry_defconfig b/arch/arm64/configs/perry_defconfig
index 135332ccf1eb..1e0888227c87 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/configs/perry_defconfig
+++ b/arch/arm64/configs/perry_defconfig
@@ -3999,7 +3999,7 @@ CONFIG_ION_MSM=y
 # Qualcomm Atheros Prima WLAN module
 #
 # CONFIG_PRIMA_WLAN is not set
-CONFIG_PRONTO_WLAN=m
+CONFIG_PRONTO_WLAN=y
 # CONFIG_PRIMA_WLAN_BTAMP is not set
 CONFIG_PRIMA_WLAN_LFR=y
 CONFIG_WLAN_FEATURE_SAE=y
-- 
2.53.0

